ITEM 1.01. ENTRY INTO A MATERIAL DEFINITIVE AGREEMENT.
 
On April 22, 2005 American Science and Engineering, Inc., announced that its Board of Directors has accelerated the vesting of certain unvested stock options previously awarded to employees. The accelerated options were issued under various equity incentive plans maintained by the Company. The acceleration of outstanding unvested options is effective immediately, on a fully-vested basis. Options held by the Chief Executive Officer, the Chief Financial Officer, all other members of management, and any other employees participating in incentive or commission compensation plans are not included in the acceleration plan. Options held by members of the Board of Directors are also excluded from the vesting acceleration. Options to purchase approximately 193,553 shares of common stock are subject to acceleration.
 
The Company is effecting this acceleration in order to provide a deserved reward to relevant employees for their significant contributions in connection with the outstanding performance of the Company.  The Board of Directors determined that such action was also in the best interests of the shareholders as it believes that such plan will engender loyalty, promote equity ownership, and encourage increased future performance by the subject employee population.
 
