FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
 
American Science and Engineering, Inc. Receives $2.9 Million Order for Parcel and Z Backscatter X-ray Inspection Systems
 
American Science and Engineering, Inc. (NASDAQ: ASEI) (AS&E), a leader in X-ray detection technology, announced today the receipt of an order from an undisclosed government client for multiple parcel and Z Backscatter X-ray inspection systems. The order totals approximately $2.9 million.
BILLERICA, Mass.  September 15, 2005
 
"We continue to gain worldwide recognition and increased demand for our patented technologies," said Anthony Fabiano, President and CEO. "Our parcel and Z Backscatter systems provide unparalleled detection capabilities to enhance security measures at high-risk locations. AS&E's range of parcel X-ray inspection systems offer comprehensive parcel inspection by combining traditional transmission X-rays with the company's signature Z Backscatter technology. AS&E's Z Backscatter systems continue to gain momentum as we further enlighten the marketplace on the advantages of this proprietary technology for cargo and vehicle inspection."
 
can be used as a stand-alone technology, or in combination with other technologies, including transmission, and Radioactive Threat Detection. Z Backscatter scanning can be implemented without the use of boom-mounted detectors, allowing for rapid drive-by screening of containers and vehicles for terrorist threats, trade fraud and contraband.
Z Backscatter Systems
 
offer varying tunnel sizes and configurations to fit various application and inspection environments. Compact X-ray units screen smaller items, including mail and briefcases; while larger, open-tunnel systems inspect oversized baggage and small cargo.  These systems are primarily used in government facilities, airports, high-security federal facilities, commercial office buildings, and convention centers.
