On July 1, 2009, Dr. Roger P. Heinisch, a Director of American Science and Engineering, Inc. (the "Company") and a member of the audit, nominating and corporate governance, and compensation committees, gave notice to the Clerk of the Company that he does not intend to stand for re-election to the Company's Board of Directors (the "Board") at the Company's 2009 annual stockholders' meeting due to personal reasons.
 
The Board intends to appoint a director to replace Dr. Heinisch, and a search is underway.  The Board expects to appoint a replacement member of the audit committee and the nominating and corporate governance committee effective concurrently with the end of Dr. Heinisch's term as a director.
